>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article", "headline": "Is BO a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 4 Points)", "description": "BO is a valid Scrabble word worth 4 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It refers to a type of fig tree (Ficus religiosa).", "datePublished": "2026-06-29", "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" }, "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" }, "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-bo-a-scrabble-word" } })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [ { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is BO a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, BO is valid in both TWL (North American) and SOWPODS (International) Scrabble dictionaries. It scores 4 points (B=3, O=1) and refers to a type of fig tree (Ficus religiosa), also known as the bodhi tree." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "What does BO mean in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "BO is a variant spelling of 'bo tree' — the sacred fig tree (Ficus religiosa) under which the Buddha achieved enlightenment. It's also an informal exclamation and a term for a fellow or pal in some dialects." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "What words can you extend BO into?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "BO extends into many useful words: BOA (5pts), BOB (7pts), BOD (6pts), BOG (6pts), BOP (7pts), BOW (8pts), BOX (12pts), BOY (8pts). BOX is particularly valuable at 12 points thanks to X(8)." } } ] })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/two-letter-words/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</a>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is BO a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 4 Points)</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Yes, BO is a valid Scrabble word worth 4 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It refers to the bo tree (Ficus religiosa) — the sacred fig under which the Buddha attained enlightenment. In Scrabble terms, B(3) makes BO a solid 2-letter play when you need to offload a B or set up extensions like BOX, BOW, or BOY.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ VALID</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">BO</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">4 points · B=3, O=1 · A type of fig tree (Ficus religiosa)</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Valid in both TWL (Tournament Word List) and SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words). BO is the sacred fig tree — also called the bodhi tree or peepul tree. One of the stronger 2-letter B words thanks to B's 3-point value.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Both</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL + SOWPODS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2 B-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In the Bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 O-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Available</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">BO Extensions: Where It Gets Powerful</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOX</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOW</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOY</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOP</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOB</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOG</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOD</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOA</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">BO Strategy: When to Play It</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">B-dump play:</span> With only 2 B-tiles in the bag, drawing B early is common. BO lets you offload B for 4 points while keeping your rack flexible for longer words next turn.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Setup for BOX:</span> Play BO near an X-friendly spot. Next turn, extend to BOX (12pts) or BOXER (14pts). You've just turned a 4-point setup into a 12+ point payoff.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Cross-scoring:</span> B on DLS scores 6 from one tile. Play BO parallel to an existing word to form valid crosswords — B touching another letter creates free points.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Compare to BE/BI/BA:</span> BO (4pts) ties with BA (4pts) as the highest 2-letter B words without high-value letters. BE (4pts) works too, but BO has stronger 3-letter extensions (BOX at 12).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">BO in Context</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Did You Know?</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The bo tree (<span class="text-white font-medium">Ficus religiosa</span>) is one of the longest-living trees in the world. The Sri Maha Bodhi in Sri Lanka is over 2,300 years old. In Scrabble, BO is equally enduring — it's been valid since the first official dictionaries and remains a reliable play for any B-heavy rack.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-po-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is PO a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 4 Points)</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-om-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is OM a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 4 Points)</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
